message.content:
Here's a **One-Pan Honey Mustard Chicken with Roasted Broccoli and Sweet Potatoes** — balanced macros, minimal cleanup, and great for meal prep.

---

## Ingredients (Serves 4)

| Ingredient | Amount |
|------------|--------|
| Chicken breast (boneless, skinless) | 1.5 lbs (680g) |
| Sweet potatoes, cubed (1-inch) | 2 large (~600g) |
| Broccoli florets | 4 cups (~400g) |
| Olive oil | 3 tbsp |
| Dijon mustard | 3 tbsp |
| Honey | 2 tbsp |
| Garlic, minced | 4 cloves |
| Smoked paprika | 1 tsp |
| Salt and black pepper | To taste |
| Lemon juice | 1 tbsp (optional finish) |

---

## Instructions

### 1. Prep & Marinate
- Whisk together **Dijon mustard, honey, 2 tbsp olive oil, garlic, paprika, salt, and pepper**
- Toss **chicken** in half the marinade; reserve the rest
- Let sit 15 minutes (or overnight)

### 2. Roast Sweet Potatoes
- Preheat oven to **425°F (220°C)**
- Toss sweet potato cubes with **1 tbsp olive oil**, salt, and pepper
- Spread on a large sheet pan; roast **15 minutes** (they take longest)

### 3. Add Chicken & Broccoli
- Push potatoes to one side; add **chicken** in center
- Toss broccoli with reserved marinade; add to pan
- Roast **20–25 minutes more** until chicken reaches **165°F (74°C)** and broccoli edges char

### 4. Finish
- Rest chicken 5 minutes, slice, and drizzle with lemon juice

---

## Nutrition Per Serving

| Macro | Amount |
|-------|--------|
| **Calories** | ~485 kcal |
| **Protein** | **42g** |
| **Carbohydrates** | 45g |
| **Fiber** | 8g |
| **Fat** | 14g |

---

## Why This Works

| Component | Benefit |
|-----------|---------|
| **Chicken** | Complete protein, leucine-rich for muscle synthesis |
| **Sweet potatoes** | Complex carbs, beta-carotene, sustained energy |
| **Broccoli** | Sulforaphane, vitamin C, volume for satiety |
| **Honey mustard glaze** | Flavor without heavy cream or butter |

---

## Variations

- **Lower carb:** Reduce sweet potato, add more broccoli or cauliflower
- **Dairy-free creamy:** Add 2 tbsp tahini to the marinade
- **Spicy:** Add ½ tsp cayenne or chili flakes
